19th Road, south side, in the 76th Street, line (19th Rd. was Bowery Road and it is located in front of house seen in both views). These two views show the farmlands, house and outbuildings which belonged to Dan'l Rapelye in 1852. View No. 1 also shows Bowery Road in the foreground, extending north and eastward. The large barn is at the N.W. corner of Twentieth Avenue and 76th Street. See other views fore more data.

March 1925
View 2: May 1923

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
